8/31/19, 3:44 PM - B A L A: This is interesting info :

1994

The President of India, Shri Shankar Dayal Sharma visited Muscat on an official trip -

When the Air India flight landed, 3 rather unusual incidents took place:

1. The Sultan of Oman never goes to the airport to receive dignitaries of any country - never. But he made an exception this time and went to the airport to receive the President of India!

2. When the flight landed, the Sultan of Oman climbed up the steps and received the President from his seat!

3 . After alighting the flight there was a car with the chauffeur standing. But the Sultan signalled the driver to move and he himself drove the car with President as his passenger!

Later when the reporters questioned the Sultan why he broke so many protocols, the Sultan replied, â€œI did not go to the airport to receive Mr. Sharma because he was Indiaâ€™s President. I studied in India and learnt so many things, when I was studying in Pune, Mr. Sharma was my Professor - that is why I did this!â€

That is the power of being a teacher.

9/2/19, 9:01 PM - Mahapatra Sir: *Dear All*

It' *s may be a hardcore recession** this time, which already spreads it's poison in the economy of India. Almost 13.67percent fall in overall economic marker is recorded. Foreign exchange, repo rate is also indicating that crisis started. Already 17Lakh of employee lost job in last quarter. Prepare and get ready for the bad times...
You can follow this steps-
1. Try to minimise extra expenses
2. Try to avoid big buying in next 6month
3. Avoid investment now, nobody knows SIP and trading will bring what amount of loss,since all are depends on the recovery.
4. Don't buy gold now, likely the price will fall from December
5. Mediocre people, small business will suffer the most, so make your budget tight.
6. Online purchase can be risky, since sites are already in loss.
7. Convert / consume all your digital money( Paytm,Gpay etcetc) into physical fund.
8. Priorities your family expenses.
9. Stay alert - snatching on roads,robbery will increase from coming festive season.
10. Try to cumulate at least your 6 month expenses from now on. The situation may be worst from November December 2019. It may persist till mid of 2020. 

11. Atlast not the least - Don't quit your job without a strong alternative on hand.

Please be alert, and circulate it like a responsible citizen, with your close friends.

9/5/19, 6:54 AM - +91 99585 15757: Good morning fellow teachers

Happy teachers day

You are a priviliged lot.ğŸ˜Š 

There are very few people in the world who get to make a difference and YOU make a difference.

We all talk about change and YOU are the harbingers of change

Society is changing and it is YOU who ensure that the fundamentals of creating a knowledgeable, empathetic and committed citizenry stay strong.

It is YOU who provide the children the finger to hold as they start their journey towards their goal with the parents doing the same on the other side.

For me it is not just the one day that the teachers are to be saluted, it is every single day that they must be credited for the selfless committment they have in nurturing the latent talents of the children of today who will lead this country to greatness tomorrow.

I am very proud to be a teacher.

Happy Teachers day with loads of love, best wishes and gratitude.
Charu Jain

9/7/19, 6:12 PM - Ranjana Mam: Why should companies recruit people over 50 for senior and responnsible positions?

Because they are more productive than those below 50!

A massive study in America found that *the most productive age in a man's life is 60 - 70*

 *From 70 - 80 is the 2nd most productive age.*

*The 3rd most productive age is 50 - 60.*

The average age of a Nobel Prize winner is 62. 

The average age of a CEO in a Fortune 500 company is 63.

*The average age of the pastors of the 100 biggest churches in America is 71*. 

*The average age of Pope's is 76*

This tells us somehow *God has designed that the best years of your life are 60 - 80!*

 *It is when you do your best work.*

*A study published in NEJM found that at 60 you reach your peak of potential and continue up to 80!*

*So, if you are between 60 - 70, or 70-80, you have the best and second best years of your life with you!*

Source: *N.Engl.J.Med 70.389(2018)*

9/15/19, 4:56 PM - Nitin Dhama: <Media omitted>
9/15/19, 4:57 PM - Swati Bhatt: At the age of 57, John B. Goodenough invented the lithium battery which powers all our smart phones, tablets and laptops - as well as electric cars.

37 years later at the age of 94, John has unveiled a new, ultra-efficient, low cost battery which uses a sodium or lithium coated glass electrolyte. It will dwarf his original invention and make it redundant.

The new glass battery will allow electric cars to go three times the distance, and recharge in minutes instead of hours. It's also far safer as it won't explode and can operate in sub-zero temperatures.

The new glass battery will power our future solar powered and electric vehicles, homes and industries.

But John isn't finished yet. He still works every day as a Professor at the University of Texas.

John believes humanity has a 30 year window to come up with an even more powerful "super battery" to take us entirely off fossil fuels, before the environmental damage we are creating becomes irreversible, and says, "I want to solve this problem before my chips are in ..... I still have time to go."

So if you ever think it's too late to be successful, just remember John B. Goodenough.

https://news.utexas.edu/2017/02/28/goodenough-introduces-new-battery-technology

10/6/19, 7:09 AM - +91 6395 249 386: <Media omitted>
10/6/19, 9:59 AM - Ankit Auto HOD: May be a repeat.     But worth reading & understand the moral 

An engineer in a car manufacturing company designs a world class car. The CEO is impressed with the outcome and praised him a lot. 

While trying to bring out the car from the manufacturing area to the showroom, they realised that the car is 2 inches taller than the entrance.

The engineer felt bad that he didn't notice this one before creating the car.

The CEO was confused on how to take it outside of the manufacturing area.

The painter said that they can bring out the car and there will be a few scratches on top of the car which could be touched up later on.

The engineer said that they can break the entrance, take the car out, and later re-do it.

The CEO was not convinced with any ideas and felt like it is a bad sign to break or scratch. 

A Watchman was observing all the drama & slowly approached the CEO.  He wanted to give an idea if they had no problem. 

They wondered what this guy would tell them that the experts could not give.

The watchman said "The car is only a few inches taller than the entrance so, simply release the air in the tyre, the height of the car will sink and can be easily taken out"...

Everyone clapped!!!

Don't analyse the problems only from an expert point of view alone.

There is always a layman's outlook that gives an alternate solution at a given point of time...

Life issues are also the same....

ğŸ˜€ Think Simple...
Do Simple and Live Simple 
Because Originally we are Happy Souls..

Release *some Air* ... It could be our 'anger' .... our 'disappointments'... our  'egos'... Our 'confusions' ..

In the end it's all about   "Adjusting The Height" ( *Attitude* ), to make things easier in life and uncomplicate the things in life. âœ¨

"Life is beautiful" .... "Enjoy every moment" ....  "Seasons change" ..... "Situations Change"..... ğŸ™ğŸ»ğŸ™ğŸ»ğŸ˜ŠğŸ‘ğŸ»âœ¨âœ¨â™»

10/8/19, 11:01 AM - +91 74286 22961: DUSSHERA means removal of ten bad qualities within a person
Kama vaasana (Lust)
Krodha (Anger)
Moha (Attachment)
Lobha (Greed)
Mada (Over Pride)
Matsara (Jealousy)
Swartha (Selfishness)
Anyaaya (Injustice)
Amanavta (Cruelty)
Ahankara (Ego)
It's also known as 'Vijaydashami' which means Vijaya over these ten bad qualities.
Happy Dussehara to all

10/25/19, 10:32 AM - Mohan Raj: Dear all,
          We are going to REGISTER your MAC ADDRESS of the devices (mobile/laptop) for the purposes of auto login feature, by a process called auto MAC register. After registering MAC address of your devices in authentication server, you need to login only once. There after it will be authenticated automatically.(LOGIN PAGE WONT APPEAR). 
AUTO MAC REGISTER SERVICE IS SCHEDULED FROM TODAY 11.00 AM TO 2.00 PM. 
DURING THIS PROCESS,
1.YOU HAVE TO LOGIN FROM THE DEVICES IN WHICH YOU WANT AUTO LOGIN.(MOBILE / LAPTOP/OFFICE DESTOP)
2.DO NOT LOGIN OTHERS DEVICE / DO NOT USE OTHERS LOGIN CREDENTIALS IN YOUR DEVICE. 
2.ONLY TWO DEVICES WILL BE AUTO REGISTERED (FIRST 2 DEVICES) FOR EACH USER. 
3.AS YOU HAVE ONLY 2 CONCURRENCY LIMIT, AFTER AUTO LOGIN IF YOU WANT USE INTERNET IN THIRD/OTHER DEVICES YOU NEED TO LOGOUT FROM ONE OF THE 2 DEVICE. (FOR LOGOUT TYPE 1.0.0.0 BROWSER). 
IF YOU HAVE PROBLEM IN AUTO LOGIN CONTACT US. 
MOHAN RAJ 
Asst Prof, Dept of CSE. 
Network support team.

11/11/19, 10:51 AM - Kamakshi Saxena: Dear Colleagues,

*Gentle Reminder for Nov 16/17 NPTEL exams*

1. Kindly take print out of hall tickets of all exams you are writing.
2. You have to bring valid govt. issued photo id card along with the printed copy of hall ticket
3. Calculators are not allowed inside the exam hall
4. On-screen calculator link is provided in hall ticket. Candidates may practise using this link
5. German I & II candidates have to bring their own headsets/earphones for audio-based questions
6. Mass Transfer Operations II : Candidates have to bring Pencil and scale for Final Exam.

All the best.

Regards.
Dr. Kamakshi

12/7/19, 8:55 PM - B A L A: _An engineer was removing the engine parts from a motorcycle._
_Suddenly he saw a famous heart surgeon in his shop. He went to him & said.. "Look at this engine... I opened its heart, took the valves out, repaired and put them back"...So why do I get such a small salary? and u get huge sums_....! 


The doctor smiled at the engineer and came close to his ear and said.... "Try the same when the engine is running_."


The engineer smiled back came close to doctors ear and said_ 
_I can pick any dead engine and make it alive . . . . . . .  can you_ ???

*Power of an Engineer*

12/28/19, 7:43 AM - +91 97553 92636: While writing a date in the upcoming year 2020, we should write in its full format, e.g. 31/01/2020 and not as 31/01/20., bcoz anyone can change it to 31/01/2000 or 31/01/2019 or in between any year to suit his convenience.

So be cautious about this. Don't write and also don't accept it in any documents, lest it could lose its importance.

This problem will persist only during the year 2020.

You are cordially invited to share your new research findings at the ICFTMME-2020 (May 29-30, 2020) organized by Department of Mechanical Engineering, SRM Institute of Science and Technology (formerly known as SRM University), Delhi-NCR campus, Ghaziabad, U.P. (INDIA) 201204.

All successfully reviewed, accepted and presented papers at  ICFTMME-2020 will be published in SPRINGER Book Series "Lecture Notes in Mechanical Engineering" (indexed in SCOPUS and submitted for indexing to Web of Science).

Conference Date: May 29-30, 2020

Kindly share the *Employability Assessment* test with the concerned students

Please share this with 2019/2020 batch students. 

Syllabus:  Aptitude, Reasoning and Verbal Ability
Questions: 60
Duration: 60 minutes

Test Link: https://tinyurl.com/qr4cf3v
Activation Code: 4SPDDMV2

*NOTE:* This is purely a SELF-ASSESSMENT TEST.
This test has been designed by a third party; NPTEL is merely sharing this.
The test results will be sent to the student's registered mail id.

Regards.
 Dr. Kamakshi

" à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤ - à¤ªà¤¿à¤¤à¤¾à¤œà¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤˜à¤° à¤ªà¥‡à¤¡à¤¼à¥‡ à¤²à¥‡à¤•à¤° à¤—à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤ªà¤¿à¤¤à¤¾à¤œà¥€ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‹ à¤à¤• à¤²à¤¾à¤– à¤°à¥à¤ªà¤¯à¥‡ à¤•à¤¾ à¤šà¥‡à¤• à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤¸à¤° à¤¨à¥‡ à¤µà¤¹ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤‰à¤¸ à¤¸à¤®à¤¯ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡ à¤µà¤¹ à¤®à¥à¤à¥‡ à¤†à¤œ à¤­à¥€ à¤¯à¤¾à¤¦ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤¸à¤° à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡ â€” "à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥à¤› à¤­à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¤¾ à¤²à¤¡à¤•à¤¾ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¬à¥à¤¦à¥à¤§à¤¿à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤«à¤¼ à¤‰à¤¸à¥‡ à¤°à¤¾à¤¸à¥à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¬à¤¤à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤œà¥à¤à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¬à¥‡à¤šà¤¤à¤¾à¥¤ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤µà¤¹ à¤¦à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‚à¤à¥¤ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¦ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤—à¤¦à¤°à¥à¤¶à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¬à¤¾à¤°à¤¹à¤µà¥€à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤ªà¥à¤¨à¤ƒ à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤Ÿ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤†à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¦ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¬à¥€. à¤ˆ. à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¦ à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤œà¤¾à¤•à¤° à¤à¤®. à¤à¤¸. à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤¶à¤¹à¤° à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤•à¤®à¥à¤ªà¤¨à¥€ à¤¶à¥à¤°à¥ à¤•à¥€à¥¤ à¤à¤• à¤ªà¤¤à¥à¤¥à¤° à¤•à¥‹ à¤¤à¤°à¤¾à¤¶à¤•à¤° à¤¸à¤° à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€à¤°à¤¾ à¤¬à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚,  à¤¸à¤° à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤à¤¸à¥‡ à¤…à¤¨à¥‡à¤• à¤…à¤¸à¤‚à¤–à¥à¤¯ à¤¹à¥€à¤°à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¨à¤¾à¤¯à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤¸à¤°, à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥‹ à¤•à¥‹à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤•à¥‹à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤£à¤¾à¤®...!!"
à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¹à¤¬ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥€ à¤†à¤à¤–à¥‹à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤†à¤¯à¥‡ à¤…à¤¶à¥à¤°à¥ à¤°à¥‚à¤®à¤¾à¤² à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¥‹à¤‚à¤›à¥‡à¥¤ 
" à¤ªà¤°à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¤ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤…à¤¦à¤­à¥à¤¤ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤• à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹à¤° à¤¶à¤¿à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤œà¥à¤à¤¾à¤¨à¤¦à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¤¾  à¤¬à¤¾à¤œà¤¾à¤° à¤­à¤°à¤¾ à¤ªà¤¡à¤¼à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‹à¤•à¤° à¤­à¥€ à¤¸à¤° à¤¨à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤°à¥à¤ªà¤¯à¤¾ à¤­à¥€ à¤¨ à¤²à¥‡à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥à¤ à¤¹à¤œà¤¾à¤°à¥‹à¤‚ à¤µà¤¿à¤¦à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¿à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹ à¤ªà¤¢à¤¼à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾, à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡à¤µà¤² à¤ªà¤¢à¤¼à¤¾à¤¯à¥‡ à¤ªà¤° à¤‰à¤¨à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤ªà¤¢à¤¼à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥€ à¤°à¥à¤šà¤¿ à¤­à¥€ à¤œà¤—à¤¾à¤ˆà¥¤ à¤µà¤¾à¤¹ à¤¸à¤° ! à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤—à¤¯à¥‡ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥‹ à¤”à¤° à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥‡ à¤†à¤¦à¤°à¥à¤¶ à¤•à¥‹à¥¤" 
à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤•à¥€ à¤“à¤° à¤¦à¥‡à¤–à¤•à¤° à¤œà¥€. à¤à¤® à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¤¹à¤¾à¥¤ 
 " à¤…à¤°à¥‡ à¤¸à¤°! à¤¯à¥‡ à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤•à¥à¤¤à¤¿ à¤¤à¤¤à¥à¤¤à¥à¤µà¤¨à¤¿à¤·à¥à¤  à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤ªà¥ˆà¤¸à¥‹à¤‚ à¤”à¤° à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¸à¤®à¥à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤­à¥‚à¤–à¥‡ à¤­à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤µà¤¿à¤¦à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¥à¥€ à¤•à¤¾ à¤­à¤²à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‹, à¤¯à¤¹à¥€ à¤à¤• à¤®à¤¾à¤¤à¥à¤° à¤‰à¤¦à¥à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¥à¤¯ à¤¥à¤¾à¥¤ " à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡à¥¤ 
" à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥‡ à¤ªà¤¿à¤¤à¤¾à¤œà¥€ à¤­à¥€ à¤‰à¤¨à¥à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤à¤• à¤¸à¤®à¤¯ à¤­à¥‚à¤–à¥‡ à¤°à¤¹ à¤²à¥‡à¤‚à¤—à¥‡, à¤ªà¤° à¤…à¤¨à¤¾à¤œ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤®à¤¿à¤²à¤¾à¤µà¤Ÿ à¤•à¤°à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¥‡à¤šà¥‡à¤‚à¤—à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚à¥¤" à¤¯à¥‡ à¤‰à¤¨à¤•à¥‡ à¤¤à¤¤à¥à¤µ à¤¥à¥‡à¥¤ à¤œà¤¿à¤¨à¥à¤¦à¤—à¥€ à¤­à¤° à¤‰à¤¸à¤•à¤¾ à¤ªà¤¾à¤²à¤¨ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤ˆà¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤¦à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ªà¤¾à¤° à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤‰à¤¸à¤•à¤¾ à¤«à¤¾à¤¯à¤¦à¤¾ à¤†à¤œ à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥‡ à¤­à¤¾à¤ˆà¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤" 
à¤¬à¤¹à¥à¤¤ à¤¦à¥‡à¤° à¤¤à¤• à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤•à¥à¤› à¤­à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¤¾  à¥¤ à¤«à¤¿à¤° à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¥‚à¤›à¤¾, - "à¤¸à¤°! à¤†à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤®à¤•à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¬à¤¦à¤² à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¯à¤¾ à¤‰à¤¸à¥€ à¤®à¤•à¤¾à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤°à¤¹à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ "
"à¤‰à¤¸à¥€ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤®à¤•à¤¾à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤°à¤¹à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤¸à¤°! "
à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¦à¤²à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤² à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤‰à¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤° à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ 
    à¤‰à¤¸ à¤‰à¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤° à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤ªà¤¿à¤¤à¤¾à¤œà¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¤¿ à¤›à¤¿à¤ªà¥€ à¤¨à¤¾à¤°à¤¾à¤œà¤—à¥€ à¤¤à¤¤à¥à¤ªà¤° à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¹à¤¬ à¤•à¥€ à¤¸à¤®à¤ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤† à¤—à¤ˆ à¥¤ 
â€Œ"à¤¤à¤¯ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤«à¤¿à¤°à¥¤ à¤¸à¤° à¤†à¤œ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥‹ à¤—à¥à¤°à¥ à¤¦à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤£à¤¾ à¤¦à¥‡ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‚à¤à¥¤ à¤‡à¤¸à¥€ à¤¶à¤¹à¤° à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥à¤› à¤«à¥à¤²à¥ˆà¤Ÿà¥à¤¸ à¤²à¥‡ à¤°à¤–à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤‰à¤¸à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤¥à¥à¤°à¥€ à¤¬à¥€. à¤à¤š. à¤•à¥‡. à¤•à¤¾ à¤®à¤•à¤¾à¤¨ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¾à¤® à¤•à¤° à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‚à¤....." 
 "à¤•à¥à¤¯à¤¾?" 
à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤”à¤° à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤² à¤¦à¥‹à¤¨à¥‹à¤‚ à¤†à¤¶à¥à¤šà¤°à¥à¤¯ à¤šà¤•à¤¿à¤¤ à¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡à¤‚à¥¤ "à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ , à¤‡à¤¤à¤¨à¥€ à¤¬à¤¡à¥€ à¤—à¥à¤°à¥ à¤¦à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤£à¤¾ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤šà¤¾à¤¹à¤¿à¤¯à¥‡ à¤®à¥à¤à¥‡à¥¤" à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤†à¤—à¥à¤°à¤¹à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥à¤µà¤• à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡à¥¤ 
à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¹à¤¬ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¶à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¹à¤¾à¤¥ à¤•à¥‹ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤¹à¤¾à¤¥ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤  " à¤¸à¤°, à¤ªà¥à¤²à¥€à¤œ....  à¤¨à¤¾ à¤®à¤¤ à¤•à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¥‡ à¤”à¤° à¤®à¥à¤à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤« à¤•à¤°à¥‡à¤‚à¥¤ à¤•à¤¾à¤® à¤•à¥€ à¤…à¤§à¤¿à¤•à¤¤à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¥€ à¤—à¥à¤°à¥ à¤¦à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤£à¤¾ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¨à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤ªà¤¹à¤²à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¬à¤¹à¥à¤¤ à¤¦à¥‡à¤° à¤¹à¥‹ à¤šà¥à¤•à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤" 
à¤«à¤¿à¤° à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥‚à¤² à¤•à¥€ à¤“à¤° à¤¦à¥‡à¤–à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥à¤ à¤‰à¤¨à¥à¤¹à¥‹à¤‚à¤¨à¥‡ à¤ªà¥‚à¤› à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾, à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤²!  à¤¤à¥à¤®à¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤¶à¤¾à¤¦à¥€ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤—à¤ˆ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¤¾? "
â€Œ" à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¸à¤°, à¤œà¤® à¤—à¤ˆ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤”à¤° à¤œà¤¬ à¤¤à¤• à¤°à¤¹à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‹ à¤…à¤šà¥à¤›à¤¾ à¤˜à¤° à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤®à¤¿à¤² à¤œà¤¾à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¤à¤¬ à¤¤à¤• à¤¶à¤¾à¤¦à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¥€à¥¤ à¤à¤¸à¥€ à¤¶à¤°à¥à¤¤ à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¸à¥à¤°à¤œà¥€ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤°à¤–à¥€ à¤¹à¥‹à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤…à¤­à¥€ à¤¤à¤• à¤¶à¤¾à¤¦à¥€ à¤•à¥€ à¤¡à¥‡à¤Ÿ à¤«à¤¿à¤•à¥à¤¸ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤•à¥€à¥¤ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤«à¤¿à¤° à¤¹à¤¾à¥…à¤² à¤­à¥€ à¤¬à¥à¤• à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ " 
à¤šà¥‡à¤¯à¤°à¤®à¥ˆà¤¨ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤«à¥‹à¤¨ à¤‰à¤ à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤•à¤¿à¤¸à¥€ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¤ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¥‡à¥¤à¤¸à¤®à¤¾à¤§à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¤• à¤šà¥‡à¤¹à¤°à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤«à¥‹à¤¨ à¤°à¤–à¤•à¤°, à¤§à¥€à¤°à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¥‡ " à¤…à¤¬ à¤šà¤¿à¤‚à¤¤à¤¾ à¤•à¥€ à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¤ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚à¥¤ à¤¤à¥à¤®à¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤°à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¥€à¤œ à¤—à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¡à¤¨ à¤•à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾à¤® à¤¹à¥‹ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ *"à¤¸à¤¾à¤—à¤° à¤²à¤¾à¤¨à¥à¤¸"* à¤¤à¥‹ à¤®à¤¾à¤²à¥‚à¤® à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥‹à¤—à¤¾! " à¤¸à¤° à¤µà¤¹ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤¬à¤¹à¥à¤¤ à¤®à¤¹à¤‚à¤—à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ... "
" à¤…à¤°à¥‡ à¤¤à¥à¤à¥‡ à¤•à¤¹à¤¾à¤ à¤ªà¥ˆà¤¸à¥‡ à¤šà¥à¤•à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤°à¥‡ à¤µà¤¿à¤¦à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¥à¥€ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¥‡ à¤•à¥à¤› à¤­à¥€ à¤•à¤° à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¸ à¤à¤• à¤†à¤µà¤¾à¤œ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥€ à¤¬à¤¾à¤¤ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤ªà¤°à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥ à¤¸à¤° à¤¤à¤¤à¥à¤µà¤¨à¤¿à¤·à¥à¤  à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚, à¤µà¥ˆà¤¸à¤¾ à¤•à¤°à¥‡à¤‚à¤—à¥‡ à¤­à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚à¥¤ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤²à¤¾à¤¨à¥à¤¸ à¤•à¤¾ à¤®à¤¾à¤²à¤¿à¤• à¤­à¥€ à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¤¾ à¤¹à¥€ à¤µà¤¿à¤¦à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¥à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤‰à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¥ˆà¤‚à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤« à¤¬à¤¤à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤¸à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤« à¤¹à¤¾à¥…à¤² à¤¹à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚, à¤­à¥‹à¤œà¤¨ à¤¸à¤¹à¤¿à¤¤ à¤¸à¤‚à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥à¤£ à¤¶à¤¾à¤¦à¥€ à¤•à¤¾ à¤–à¤°à¥à¤šà¤¾ à¤­à¥€ à¤‰à¤ à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥€ à¤œà¤¿à¤®à¥à¤®à¥‡à¤¦à¤¾à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤ à¤²à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤‰à¤¸à¤¨à¥‡... à¤µà¤¹ à¤­à¥€ à¤¸à¥à¤µà¤–à¥à¤¶à¥€ à¤¸à¥‡à¥¤ à¤¤à¥à¤® à¤•à¥‡à¤µà¤² à¤¤à¤¾à¤°à¥€à¤– à¤¬à¤¤à¤¾à¤“ à¤”à¤° à¤¸à¤¾à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤²à¥‡à¤•à¤° à¤œà¤¾à¤“à¥¤ 
"à¤¬à¤¹à¥‚à¤¤ à¤¬à¤¹à¥‚à¤¤ à¤§à¤¨à¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¾à¤¦ à¤¸à¤°à¥¤" à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤² à¤…à¤¤à¥à¤¯à¤§à¤¿à¤• à¤–à¥à¤¶à¥€ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¤¾à¤¥ à¤œà¥‹à¤¡à¤¼à¤•à¤° à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¤¾à¥¤ 
"à¤§à¤¨à¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¾à¤¦ à¤®à¥à¤à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚, à¤¤à¥à¤®à¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤°à¥‡ à¤ªà¤¿à¤¤à¤¾à¤¶à¥à¤°à¥€ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¦à¥‹ à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤²! à¤¯à¥‡ à¤‰à¤¨à¤•à¥€ à¤ªà¥à¤£à¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤¹ à¤”à¤° à¤®à¥à¤à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤µà¤šà¤¨ à¤¦à¥‹ à¤°à¤¾à¤¹à¥à¤²! à¤¸à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤‚à¤¤à¤¿à¤® à¤¸à¤¾à¤‚à¤¸ à¤¤à¤• à¤¤à¥à¤® à¤‰à¤¨à¥à¤¹à¥‡à¤‚ à¤…à¤²à¤— à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤•à¤°à¥‹à¤—à¥‡ à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤¨à¥à¤¹à¥‡à¤‚

2/12/20, 1:20 PM - Dinesh Babu: IT Process Enhancement: Employee Data for HRMS (New ERP): TeamDeck

We are presenting here a portal:  TeamDeck (https://teamdeck.srmist.edu.in), to provide every employee an electronic facility to update his / her personal details, new qualification acquired, FDP / Seminar attended etc.

Henceforth, this facility will be a part of HRMS (Human Resource Management System) of New ERP.

We need to capture all the employee data (Teaching / Non-Teaching) in this portal for future usage in HRMS & also for IQAC analysis related various ranking and accreditation process. This can be accessed by all employees of SRMIST across all campuses by using NetID.

Request you to complete the data submission & keep this updated as & when required. You can login into this portal using their respective NetID login credentials and complete the data submission on or before Feb 20, 2020.

Kindly send email to dineshbk@srmist.edu.in  for any clarification / issues noticed.

Thank you for your cooperation.

Regards,

K.DINESH BABU
Network & ERP Support

2/14/20, 1:42 PM - +91 94133 50811: SIH 2020 has re-opened 174 Software and 46 Hardware Problem Statements  for additional idea submissions. Hence SPOC can submit additional 2 Software nominations and 2 Hardware nominations. The last date for Software nomination is 18th Feb while for Hardware is 09th March.  The nominations can be sent to hod.cse.ncr@srmist.edu.in and veenak1@srmist.edu.in. The list of problem statements which are eligible for the second round of submission, are ONLY visible in the sih portal. https://www.sih.gov.in/sih2020PS.
Ideas have to be submitted in 3 slides Powerpoint Presentation in  pdf format as per SIH template only which is provided at SIH portal.  More than one idea for a single problem will not be accepted.
HODs of all the departments are requested  to motivate their students  for submission of idea solutions by the students. Students can form a team of 6 members with multidisciplinary departments  having essentially one female candidate. 
SIH-Coordinator
Veena Khandelwal

Next two weeks are crucial for India.
If we take adequate precaution and break the chain then we can tide the Corona virus Outbreak else we have a big problem in hand especially for the elderly population
So far so good. India has done well so far in its fight to contain Corona Virus. Now we are in stage 3 in which Virus spreads through social contacts & in social gatherings. This is most critical stage & number of confirmed cases spread exponentially everyday like what happened in Italy between last week of February & second week of March. From 300 to 10,000. If India is not able to manage this stage for next 3 to 4 weeks then we could have confirmed cases not in Thousands but in Lakhs. This next one month is crucial. That is why most events & public gatherings have been closed till 15th April.

Just because schools are closed avoid getting that compulsive travel & Holiday bug. Holidays will come next year too why try your luck with Corona specially with children. Marriage functions, Birthday parties etc can wait. Donâ€™t try your luck & that bravado that nothing will happen to me. Next 30 days will be most crucial in medical History of India. Take all precautions while at home & while outside for any important work. Precaution is not panic.

Be a responsible citizen by following & educating others to remain careful for next one month.

3/18/20, 7:07 AM - Anna Alphy: Sharing a list of surface contact points in daily life, where either multiple or unknown people contact. The Virus is spreading from surfaces mainly, and  lives up 6 days on surfaces outside the host:

1.  Morning milk bags. 
2. Elevator buttons. 
3. Door bells. 
4. Newspapers.
5. Car door after wash.
6. Garbage can exchange with housekeeping staff (also their ingress into housing society, and movement from house to house).
7. Raw vegetable and fruits purchased. 
8. Shop counters. 
9. Office pantry, lunchroom, washroom, and door handles.
10. Garden seats. 
11. Play area swings, etc. (though for an unknown reason, young children thankfully are less affected)
12. Maids touching multiple surfaces at home.
13. All door knobs.
14. Packets of Delivery boys - Amazon, Swiggy, etc.
15. Any shopping packets.
16. Currency notes and coins. 
17. Uber, Auto, etc. 
18. Bus and train handles
19. Shoes, etc., which may step on spit.
20. If travelling by air, then multiple points from departing terminal to arrival terminal. 21. Biometric attendance machines. 22. Electric switches , keyboard and mouse

India has likely hit the exponential upward part of the contagion, and the precautions in the  next 2- 4 weeks are very important.  Pls FWD to all
3/18/20, 7:28 AM - +91 99585 15757: Sharing a list of surface contact points in daily life, where either multiple or unknown people contact. The Virus is spreading from surfaces mainly, and  lives up 6 days on surfaces outside the host:

1.  Morning milk bags. 
2. Elevator buttons. 
3. Door bells. 
4. Newspapers.
5. Car door after wash.
6. Garbage can exchange with housekeeping staff (also their ingress into housing society, and movement from house to house).
7. Raw vegetable and fruits purchased. 
8. Shop counters. 
9. Office pantry, lunchroom, washroom, and door handles.
10. Garden seats. 
11. Play area swings, etc. (though for an unknown reason, young children thankfully are less affected)
12. Maids touching multiple surfaces at home.
13. All door knobs.
14. Packets of Delivery boys - Amazon, Swiggy, etc.
15. Any shopping packets.
16. Currency notes and coins. 
17. Uber, Auto, etc. 
18. Bus and train handles
19. Shoes, etc., which may step on spit.
20. If travelling by air, then multiple points from departing terminal to arrival terminal. 21. Biometric attendance machines. 22. Electric switches , keyboard and mouse

3/18/20, 11:03 AM - DR Sir WhatsApp No: NamasteğŸ™

Next 15-20 days
Corona Virus precautions for house-holds:

1. Wash milk bags the moment we take it & wash your hands while you are at it.

2. Consider cancelling newspapers.

3. Keep a separate tray for couriers. Courier person can place the envelope/pkg in the tray and courier may be left untouched for at least 24 hours. 

4. Instruct maids not to touch main door. On entering the home, she has to immediatly wash hands thoroughly, before touching other things . After that, wipe the calling-bell switch with a cleaning fluid :)

3. Avoid getting swiggy, amazon etc as far as possible.

4. Wash all fruits and vegitables once we bring them home.

5. Remote, phone and keyboards are the most highly contaminated elements in our house. Clean them at least once a day using cleaning fluid.

6. Wash hands frequently when in house or in office. Once every hour at least.

7. Avoid public transport as far as possible. Even Ola and Uber may be used when absolutely unavoidable.

8. Avoid gyms, swimming pool and other exercise areas, where surface contact or air-borne contamination is inevitable.

9. Cancel tuitions, dance/music classes, etc.

10. When you return home from office, shopping, etc. discard your clothes and wash your hands and feet thoroughly.

11. Most importantly do not touch hands anywhere on face. Inform children and parents.

12. Ask senior citizens to stop going for the routine walking exercise. 

Lets all be alert as we will enter stage 3 soon which is an outbreak of infection in community (from individual cases)

3/18/20, 7:35 PM - +91 99585 15757: Forwarded message. 

Best explanation I have read about the corona virus: 
Feeling confused as to why Coronavirus is a bigger deal than Seasonal flu?
 Here it is in a nutshell. I hope this helps. Feel free to share this to others who donâ€™t understand...
It has to do with RNA sequencing.... I.e. genetics.

Seasonal flu is an â€œall human virusâ€. The DNA/RNA chains that make up the virus are recognized by the human immune system. This means that your body has some immunity to it before it comes around each year... you get immunity two ways...through exposure to a virus, or by getting a flu shot.
Novel viruses, come from animals.... the WHO tracks novel viruses in animals, (sometimes for years watching for mutations). Usually these viruses only transfer from animal to animal (pigs in the case of H1N1) (birds in the case of the Spanish flu). But once, one of these animal viruses mutates, and starts to transfer from animals to humans... then itâ€™s a problem, Why? Because we have no natural or acquired immunity.. the RNA sequencing of the genes inside the virus isnâ€™t human, and the human immune system doesnâ€™t recognize it so, we canâ€™t fight it off.

Now.... sometimes, the mutation only allows transfer from animal to human, for years itâ€™s only transmission is from an infected animal to a human before it finally mutates so that it can now transfer human to human... once that happens..we have a new contagion phase. And depending on the fashion of this new mutation, thats what decides how contagious, or how deadly itâ€™s gonna be..
H1N1 was deadly....but it did not mutate in a way that was as deadly as the Spanish flu. Itâ€™s RNA was slower to mutate and it attacked its host differently, too.
Fast forward.
Now, here comes this Coronavirus... it existed in animals only, for nobody knows how long...but one day, at an animal market, in Wuhan China, in December 2019, it mutated and made the jump from animal to people. At first, only animals could give it to a person... But here is the scary part.... in just TWO WEEKS it mutated again and gained the ability to jump from human to human. Scientists call this quick ability, â€œslipperyâ€
This Coronavirus, not being in any form a â€œhumanâ€ virus (whereas we would all have some natural or acquired immunity). Took off like a rocket. And this was because, Humans have no known immunity...doctors have no known medicines for it.
And it just so happens that this particular mutated animal virus, changed itself in such a way the way that it causes great damage to human lungs..
Thatâ€™s why Coronavirus is different from seasonal flu, or H1N1 or any other type of influenza.... this one is slippery AF. And itâ€™s a lung eater...And, itâ€™s already mutated AGAIN, so that we now have two strains to deal with, strain s, and strain L....which makes it twice as hard to develop a vaccine.
We really have no tools in our shed, with this. History has shown that fast and immediate closings of public places has helped in the past pandemics. Philadelphia and Baltimore were reluctant to close events in 1918 and they were the hardest hit in the US during the Spanish Flu.
Factoid: Henry VIII stayed in his room and allowed no one near him, till the Black Plague passed...(honestly...I understand him so much better now). Just like us, he had no tools in his shed, except social isolation...
And let me end by saying....right now itâ€™s hitting older folks harder... but this genome is so slippery...if it mutates again (and it will). Who is to say, what it will do next.
Be smart folks... acting like youâ€™re unafraid is so not sexy right now.
#flattenthecurve. Stay home folks... and share this to those that just are not catching on.

à¤‡à¤¸à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤†à¤ª à¤”à¤° à¤¹à¤® à¤¸à¥à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥ à¤²à¤—à¤¨à¥‡ à¤µà¤¾à¤²à¥‡ à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤•à¥à¤¤à¤¿ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤¬à¥ˆà¤ à¥‡ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¤à¤¬ à¤­à¥€ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤µà¤¹ à¤‡à¤¨à¥à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‚à¤¬à¥‡à¤¶à¤¨ à¤ªà¥€à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¤¡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤¹à¤® à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤‡à¤¨à¥à¤«à¥‡à¤•à¥à¤¶à¤¨ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤²à¥‡ à¤†à¤ à¤”à¤° à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤ªà¤°à¤¿à¤µà¤¾à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¦à¤¸à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¯à¤¾ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¤²à¥€à¤—à¥à¤¸ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¦à¥‡ à¤†à¤ à¥¤ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤¹à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤­à¥€ à¤ªà¤¤à¤¾ à¤¤à¤¬ à¤šà¤²à¥‡à¤—à¤¾ à¤œà¤¬ à¤¬à¥€à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤•à¥à¤·à¤£ à¤¦à¤¿à¤–à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¥‡à¤‚à¤—à¥‡ à¥¤

3/19/20, 9:01 AM - +91 86673 81913: Good Morning 

Dear All

*Most serious alert to all of us* 

It is our individual responsibilities to protect ourself and our family, surroundings

Even after government/organization/industries taking safety measures as work from home, controlling crowds, holidays , *shutdown many activities to isolate people at home* but still people are travelling around the country.
*Job related and important travel can't be avoided*

Also people admitted in hospital for COVID19 check are trying to escape hospitals *due to lack of facilities in hospital*

*NOTE*: Only two cities in Italy were in COVID19 alert initially and when the government taken decision to isolate, people from those cities travelled to their home town around the country.. this is how situation became worst in Italy from starting stage.... *the same is happening right now in our country also*

*Though we can't be united physically closer We can be united mentally and everyone together can win this disaster* ğŸ’ª

Humanity, self awareness, keep surroundings clean and by following all safety measures instructed by W.H.O. we can protect our family...  Please be cautious and let us fix our future

SRM-IST, NCR campus is planning to conduct a fully funded conference on â€œApplication of Technical Terms in Engineering and Managementâ€ à¤‡à¤‚à¤œà¥€à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤°à¤¿à¤‚à¤— à¤”à¤° à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¬à¤‚à¤§à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¤à¤•à¤¨à¥€à¤•à¥€ à¤¶à¤¬à¥à¤¦à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¾ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¯à¥‹à¤—â€ in association with Commission for Scientific and Technical Terminology-Ministry of Human Resources Development (CSTT-MHRD) tentatively on 26-27 June 2020.   

This conference will be held in Hindi language and would be beneficial for the researchers to explore their research potential in Hindi also.

*Participants will not be charged any kind of fees for this conference.  Reimbursement for T.A. / D.A. and accommodation will be paid to out station participants as per CSTT-MHRD norms.*

List of proposed participants for the conference is to be submitted along with the proposal as per CSTT norms.

So, if you are interested to submit a research paper for presentation in the conference, kindly submit your information on the link given below:

Just basic guidlelines of isolation, 

No complacency but social distancing. 
 
Everyone, especially 
Senior citizens to stay home

+ Janta curfew on this Sunday 22/03/2020 as a practice/drill 7am-9pm
No going out of home during this time. Spread this msg as much as possible. each person tell 10 other people everyday for next 2 days. 

+ Expressing thankfulness to service providers - medical, home delivery, media etc, at 5pm on Sunday 22/3/2020 by standing outside your home /balcony and clapping or ringing bells/ plates to salute and encourage them.

+Speak to doc on phone if anything, avoid using medical resources 

+ Take economic interest of those who work for you as this situation will worsen the financial situation of many, e.g. don't cut wages, decide humanely/sensitively. 

+ Supply of milk, food, medicine will not be stopped therefore pls do not hoard. Buy as you normally buy, do not do panic buying.

+ Put all energy in stopping corona. And fight against this global pandemic
Save yourse, save the country, save the world

3/20/20, 2:34 PM - Vikas Vidhyarthy Civil: Corona- the teacher reminds us of our Indian traditions and age-old practices

*1. Why the bathrooms and toilets were *outside* our houses and not *inside*

*2. Why we should not touch anything or anybody when we return from a barbershop or a funeral. You may return to normalcy *only* after having a bath immediately.*

*3. Why the footwear has to be kept outside the house and not inside.*

*4. Why we have to wash our hands and feet when we returned from schools or outside after playing.*

*5. Why a mandatory 10 days isolation / quarantine (especially at a birth or death) in traditional households.*

*6. Why the households must not cook if there's a dead body inside the house.*
 
*7. Why the washing of discarded clothes has to be done outside the house and not inside.*

*8. Why was it mandatory to be clean and have bath before cooking for the house.*

*9. Why once you have had bath, you were not supposed to physically touch those who did not.*

Maintaining physical hygiene, social distance and cleanliness were laughed at, ridiculed, insulted, systematically breaking these traditions brick by brick, forcing people to discard these rituals for the fear of being isolated and *force fit* into a society blindly aping the Western way of life. 

Now, all these habits &  routines followed by our forefathers from time immemorial stand validated.ğŸ‘

3/23/20, 8:41 PM - +91 86673 81913: Dear All,
A small recommendation from another group - seems practical to me : Use your left hand on door handles, carts, knobs, taps etc. to protect your right hand from germs. The majority of face contact is made with the right hand, if you are a right hander. Understand that they managed to spread this message widely in South Korea, which was well followed. Stay safe!!

3/23/20, 10:38 PM - Vikas Vidhyarthy Civil: This is how we fight together. (from the  news paper of 23th March)

1.  After, the notification by GoI to cap the retail prices Mask at â‚¹10 and hand sanitizer at â‚¹100 per 200 ml, leading FMCG companies such as HUL, Reckitt Benckiser, ITC, Godrej and Dabur has slashed their prices of sanitizer by upto 70%. 

2.  Leading liquor Companies like Amrut Distilleries and John Distilleries has approached the GoI license to manufacturer sanitizers. (Ethyl alcohol is a key ingredient of both liquor and sanitizer.)

3. Many technical institutes (including IITs, NITs, IACS, Pharmaceutical Science colleges) in India are already making their own senitizer.

4. Mahindra and Mahindra  has  started manufacturing ventilators in his car manufacturing factories. Internationally, Volkswagen, GM, Ford, and Tesla are already doing this.

5. The GoI, Telecommunication Companies and video streaming companies (like youtube, amazon, hotstar) are talking together and planning to temporarily migrate from HD to SD streaming. So that the load on the internet bandwidth can be reduced.

6. GoI has asked and provided funds to state governments to purchase medical equipments as per need. In addition to that he GoI has also purchased 1200 ventilators (as of 22 March) as a buffer stock in case of emergency requirement by any of the state government.

7. Mahindra Holidays will also offer its resorts as temporary care facility and hospital.

8.  The Drugs Controller General of India (DGCI) is assisting the Pharmaceutical Companies in finding a cure of CoViD-19.  The DGCI has offered 7 measures for speeding up the process from giving Fast Track approval for repurposed drug to waving animal Street and offering flexible pathway which earlier would have taken months.

9. According to the minuts of meeting held by Textile Ministry, supply order was placed for 1 million 3-ply masks. Moreover, the HLL lifecare -- the government's nodal agency for the procuring Personal Protective Equipments has floated a tender for 725000 body covers, 1.5 million N-95 masks and 1 million 3-ply masks.

10. The government has asked Defence and Atomic Research labs to join the national effort to find a solution to deal with the Covid-19 virus outbreak. The country's biotechnology, science, and technology research institutions have also been tasked to source clinical samples from any government approved clinical testing sites and do research on the virus. The decision was taken by the empowered committee for OPD 19 response led by Dr Vinod Paul member of Niti Aayog and K vijayraghavan principal scientific advisor to the government. The Pune-based National Institute of virology has already sequenced the genome of the virus -- India being 5th country to do so --  which is essential to do research on finding test drugs and vaccines.

11. The labour ministry is working on comprehensive package to provide relief to workers and employers in the organised sector, as the the covide-19 outbreak shuts factories and offices takes a toll on jobs and impact livelihoods. An announcement could be made as early as this week.

Just imagine,if there is no network, and you are unable to connect yourself with your phones,laptops,internet etc just for an hour, how the life will be in such critical situations?As internet & Mobile phones are todays most important needs,of every human being.To know about your loved ones,(near/distant) to work from your home, to buy important medicines & other things, U need Network! ğŸ“±ğŸ“²ğŸ“³
When most of the companies have declared work from home, Our technical/non technical team are working constantly that too from the office, sites etc.Their families are scared, in these circumstances but they can't sit at home! It's only because of their efforts, YOU, ME & ALL can share,post & circulate messeges, Smile, talk to our friends and family, know about the world...They haven't isolated themselves for us....They bring the world to us..

3/24/20, 10:03 PM - Pankaj Varshne: I can not hold myself to share this among you all. As Currently lockdown and curfew imposed at many places. But you need to go out for daily essentials. Kindly follow these ONEs.

ONE person: Identify one adult in a family for going out. Only he or she will go out. NOBODY ELSE.

ONE dress: Use only one dress and same dress every time you go out. Use full length dress. Don't mix this dress with your other dresses. 

ONE wallet: Use only one wallet. Don't mix these currency, coins and cards with other which already are there at home.

ONE shopping bag: Use only one and same shopping bag every time. 

ONE vehicle: Use same vehicle and key. Avoid public transportation.

ONE go: Avoid going out multiple times. Finish all your work in one go.

Avoid taking mobile phone or restrict using it.

Avoid crowding and come back immediately once you finish your work.

Use your non dominant hand or elbow to open the door or push the buttons. 

Once you come back: Keep your dress, wallet, bags, keys in a separate bag. Don't mix with others. Do thorough hand wash and face wash before touching anything and anyone. Clean your mobile phone surface with sanitizer. Best is to avoid mobile phone. 

Remember, we CAN'T AVOID exposure but we CAN REDUCE exposure.ğŸ™

As of tomorrow, do not leave home for bread for anything, because the worst begins, the incubation date is met and many positives will start to come out and many people can get it, so it is very important to stay home and not relate to  nobody, being very careful is very important and very crucial

 From March 23 to April 3 we must take care of ourselves as we will be
 at the peak of the virus is two weeks, normally in those two weeks all infected will appear then there are two weeks of calm and then two weeks where it decreases.

3/28/20, 6:51 PM - +91 88600 21873: Someone gave a suggestion on "Interact with Prime Minister"

Majority of people are fasting as it is Navratri and always give gifts and money to Kanjaks on Ashtmi and Navami. This year we have no option so depending on the number of kanjaks we give gift to, all of us can donate the same amount in Pradhan Mantri fund, either through paytm or NEFT(Govt. can issue the number). I give it to 11 girls and everyone gives minimum Rs. 11, thus making it 11x11=Rs. 121. If one person will give Rs. 121 then even if only 2 crore people(out of 130 crores) donate, it will make Rs. 242,00,00,000.(Rs. Two Hundred Forty Two Crores) for Corona Victims/Poor people. 

No load on a single person but together we can bring a huge difference

à¤ªà¤° à¤¹à¤° à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤à¥€à¤¯ à¤•à¥‹
à¤¯à¤¾à¤¦ à¤°à¤–à¤¨à¤¾ à¤šà¤¾à¤¹à¤¿à¤ à¤•à¤¿ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤”à¤° à¤šà¥€à¤¨à¥€ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤•à¥à¤¦à¤°à¤¤ à¤•à¥‡ à¤–à¤² à¤¨à¤¾à¤¯à¤• à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤‡à¤¨à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¤° à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤•à¥€ à¤¦à¥‚à¤°à¥€ à¤¬à¤¨à¤¾à¤ 
à¤°à¤–à¥‡à¤‚à¥¤
à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¶à¤‚à¤˜à¤¾à¤ˆ = 839 km

à¤ªà¤¾à¤¸ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¥€à¤œà¤¿à¤‚à¤—/ à¤¶à¤‚à¤˜à¤¾à¤ˆ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾ à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤­à¤¾à¤µ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ 
à¤²à¥‡à¤•à¤¿à¤¨ à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€, à¤ˆà¤°à¤¾à¤¨, à¤¯à¥‚à¤°à¥‹à¤ª à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¥‹à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤²à¥‹à¤—à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥€ à¤®à¥ƒà¤¤à¥à¤¯à¥ à¤”à¤° à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥‡ à¤µà¤¿à¤¶à¥à¤µ à¤•à¥€ à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾ à¤¬à¤°à¥à¤¬à¤¾à¤¦.

à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤­à¥€ à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ªà¤¾à¤°à¤¿à¤• à¤•à¥à¤·à¥‡à¤¤à¥à¤° à¤¸à¥à¤°à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤¤

à¤•à¥à¤› à¤¤à¥‹ à¤—à¥œà¤¬à¥œ à¤¹à¥ˆ,
à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¦à¥‹à¤· à¤¦à¥‡ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾.
à¤®à¤¿à¤¤à¥à¤°à¥‹à¤‚ à¤à¥‚à¤ à¥€ à¤…à¤«à¤µà¤¾à¤¹à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¹à¤•à¤¾à¤µà¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤†à¤•à¤° à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¤¾ à¤§à¥ˆà¤°à¥à¤¯ à¤¨ à¤–à¥‹à¤à¤‚à¥¤ à¤ªà¥‹à¤¸à¥à¤Ÿ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¶à¥‡à¤¯à¤° à¤•à¤° à¤¸à¤­à¥€ à¤¤à¤• à¤¸à¤¹à¥€ à¤œà¤¾à¤¨à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¥‡à¤·à¤¿à¤¤ à¤•à¤°à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¤¾ à¤µà¤¿à¤µà¥‡à¤• à¤”à¤° à¤§à¥ˆà¤°à¥à¤¯ à¤¹à¥€ à¤†à¤ªà¤•à¤¾ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤ˆà¤¶à¥à¤µà¤° à¤”à¤° à¤¸à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤ªà¤° à¤­à¤°à¥‹à¤¸à¤¾ à¤°à¤–à¥‡à¤‚à¥¤ à¤˜à¤° à¤®à¥‡à¤‚  à¤°à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚, à¤¸à¥à¤°à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤¤ à¤°à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤

 à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¸à¥‡ 10 à¤•à¥œà¥‡ à¤¸à¤µà¤¾à¤² : (à¤¸à¤µà¤¾à¤² à¤¨à¤‚ 6,7,8,9 à¤…à¤µà¤¶à¥à¤¯ à¤ªà¥à¥‡à¤‚)

1) à¤œà¤¹à¤¾à¤‚ à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥€ à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤‡à¤¸à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤­à¤¾à¤µà¤¿à¤¤ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤°à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆ, à¤µà¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤²à¤¾à¤µà¤¾ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¾? à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥€ à¤°à¤¾à¤œà¤§à¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤†à¤–à¤¿à¤° à¤‡à¤¸à¤¸à¥‡ à¤…à¤›à¥‚à¤¤à¥€ à¤•à¥ˆà¤¸à¥‡ à¤°à¤¹ à¤—à¤¯à¥€? 

2) à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¾à¤°à¤‚à¤­à¤¿à¤• à¤…à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥€ à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¬à¤¾à¤°à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤›à¥à¤ªà¤¾à¤¯à¤¾?

4) à¤‡à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤®à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤µà¤¾à¤²à¥‡ à¤¡à¥‰à¤•à¥à¤Ÿà¤° à¤”à¤° à¤ªà¤¤à¥à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤•à¥‹ à¤–à¤¾à¤®à¥‹à¤¶ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾? à¤ªà¤¤à¥à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤•à¥‹ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤—à¤¾à¤¯à¤¬ à¤¹à¥€ à¤•à¤° à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ?

5)  à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤œà¤¬ à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤¸à¤¾à¤à¤¾ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‹ à¤•à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤‰à¤¸à¤¨à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤¸à¤¾à¤à¤¾ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾? à¤®à¤¨à¤¾ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾? 

6) à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ, à¤‡à¤¸à¥‡ à¤›à¥à¤ªà¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ WHO  à¤•à¥‡ à¤•à¤®à¥à¤¯à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¸à¥à¤Ÿ à¤¨à¤¿à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¤• à¤•à¤¾ à¤‰à¤ªà¤¯à¥‹à¤— à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾? WHO à¤•à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¿à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¤• à¤œà¤¨à¤µà¤°à¥€ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ "à¤¬à¥€à¤à¤¿à¤‚à¤— (à¤šà¥€à¤¨)" à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¤° à¤°à¤¹à¥‡ à¤¥à¥‡ ..... ?????? 7) "à¤•à¤¿à¤¸à¥€ à¤­à¥€ à¤…à¤‚à¤¤à¤°à¤°à¤¾à¤·à¥à¤Ÿà¥à¤°à¥€à¤¯ à¤‰à¤¡à¤¼à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤—à¤¾à¤‡à¤¡à¤²à¤¾à¤‡à¤¨ à¤œà¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥€ à¤œà¤°à¥‚à¤°à¤¤ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¥ˆ, à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚à¤•à¤¿ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ" ....à¤à¤¸à¤¾ à¤Ÿà¥à¤µà¥€à¤Ÿ 11 à¤œà¤¨à¤µà¤°à¥€ à¤¤à¤• WHO à¤•à¤°à¤¤à¤¾ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¥¤ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ ???  à¤†à¤œ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¬à¤¿à¤¤ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¤¿ à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¤¾à¤¨à¤µ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ... à¤¤à¥‹ à¤«à¤¿à¤° WHO à¤¨à¥‡ à¤à¥‚à¤  à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¬à¥‹à¤²à¤¾ ????

8) à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤à¤•à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ 50,00,000 à¤²à¥‹à¤—à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¬à¤¿à¤¨à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤¡à¤¿à¤•à¤² à¤œà¤¾à¤‚à¤š à¤•à¤¿à¤ "à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤²à¤—-à¤…à¤²à¤— à¤¹à¤¿à¤¸à¥à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚" à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤­à¥‡à¤œà¤¾ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾ ..???  

9) à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ 6 à¤«à¤°à¤µà¤°à¥€ à¤¤à¤• à¤®à¤¾à¤®à¥‚à¤²à¥€ à¤•à¥‡à¤¸ à¤¥à¤¾à¥¤ à¤à¤•à¤¾à¤à¤• à¤šà¥€à¤¨à¥€ 'à¤¹à¤® à¤šà¥€à¤¨à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚, à¤¹à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤—à¤²à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤‡à¤à¥¤' à¤ªà¥à¤²à¥‡à¤•à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤¡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡ à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤¯à¤Ÿà¤¨ à¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤² 'à¤¸à¤¿à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤‘à¤« à¤²à¤µ' à¤•à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¾à¤® à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¤¶à¤¹à¥‚à¤° à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¥‹à¤—à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹ à¤—à¤²à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤ªà¤¹à¥à¤‚à¤šà¥‡ ???

10) à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥€ à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾  à¤†à¤œ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤”à¤° WHO à¤•à¥‹ à¤¸à¤‚à¤¦à¥‡à¤¹ à¤•à¥€ à¤¨à¤œà¤° à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¦à¥‡à¤– à¤°à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤”à¤° à¤¤à¤¾à¤œà¥à¤œà¥à¤¬ à¤¦à¥‡à¤–à¤¿à¤ à¤•à¤¿ à¤à¤• à¤¹à¥€ à¤¦à¤¿à¤¨ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤”à¤° WHO, à¤¦à¥‹à¤¨à¥‹à¤‚ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤•à¥€ à¤¤à¤¾à¤°à¥€à¤« à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤‰à¤¤à¤° à¤†à¤! à¤•à¥à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤®à¤¹à¤œ à¤¸à¤‚à¤¯à¥‹à¤— à¤¹à¥ˆ? 

11)  à¤”à¤° à¤‡à¤¸à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤—à¤²à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¦à¤¿à¤¨ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤°à¤¾à¤œà¤¦à¥‚à¤¤ à¤Ÿà¥à¤µà¥€à¤Ÿ à¤•à¤° à¤‰à¤®à¥à¤®à¥€à¤¦ à¤•à¤°à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤•à¤¿ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤‡à¤‚à¤Ÿà¤°à¤¨à¥‡à¤¶à¤¨à¤² à¤•à¤®à¥à¤¯à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤‰à¤¸à¤•à¥€ à¤ªà¥ˆà¤°à¤µà¥€ à¤•à¤°à¥‡à¥¤ à¤†à¤–à¤¿à¤° à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚? à¤¨à¥‡à¤¹à¤°à¥‚ à¤•à¥€ à¤à¤• à¤—à¤²à¤¤à¥€ à¤•à¤¾ à¤–à¤¾à¤®à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤œà¤¾ à¤¹à¤® à¤­à¥à¤—à¤¤ à¤šà¥à¤•à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤®à¥‹à¤¦à¥€ à¤¸à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤¹à¥ˆ, à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤®à¥à¤®à¥€à¤¦ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤µà¤¹ à¤•à¤® à¤¸à¥‡ à¤•à¤® à¤µà¤¹ à¤—à¤²à¤¤à¥€ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¦à¥‹à¤¹à¤°à¤¾à¤à¤—à¥€? 

12) à¤¸à¤¾à¤°à¥à¤• à¤¸à¥‡ à¤²à¥‡à¤•à¤° G-20 à¤¤à¤• à¤•à¥€ à¤¬à¥ˆà¤ à¤• à¤ªà¥€à¤à¤® à¤®à¥‹à¤¦à¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤•à¤¹à¤¨à¥‡ à¤ªà¤° à¤¹à¥‹ à¤°à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆâ€Œà¥¤ à¤¸à¤‚à¤•à¤Ÿ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤®à¤¯ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤µà¤°à¥à¤²à¥à¤¡ à¤²à¥€à¤¡à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤‰à¤­à¤°à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€, à¤œà¤°à¥à¤®à¤¨à¥€, à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¥‡à¤¨, à¤«à¥à¤°à¤¾à¤‚à¤¸, à¤¬à¥à¤°à¤¿à¤Ÿà¥‡à¤¨, à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤¤à¤• à¤œà¤¬ à¤•à¥ˆà¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¿à¤¬à¤Ÿà¤¨à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤…à¤¸à¤«à¤² à¤¹à¥‹ à¤°à¤¹à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤ªà¥€à¤à¤® à¤®à¥‹à¤¦à¥€ à¤•à¥€ à¤ªà¤¹à¤² à¤ªà¤° à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤‡à¤¸à¤¸à¥‡ à¤•à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¬à¥‡à¤¹à¤¤à¤° à¤¤à¤°à¥€à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¡à¥€à¤² à¤•à¤° à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ 

à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤‡à¤¸à¥€ à¤•à¤¾ à¤«à¤¾à¤¯à¤¦à¤¾ à¤‰à¤ à¤¾à¤•à¤° à¤¯à¤¹ à¤šà¤¾à¤¹à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤•à¤¿ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¤¤ à¤‡à¤‚à¤Ÿà¤°à¤¨à¥‡à¤¶à¤¨à¤² à¤•à¤®à¥à¤¯à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤‰à¤¸à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤›à¥‚à¤¤à¤ªà¤¨ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¦à¥‚à¤° à¤•à¤°à¥‡à¥¤ à¤…à¤¬ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¥‹à¤—à¤¾à¥¤  à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¸à¤‚à¤¦à¥‡à¤¹ à¤•à¥‡ à¤˜à¥‡à¤°à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤”à¤° à¤°à¤¹à¥‡à¤—à¤¾!

 à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤ªà¤° à¤¹à¤¾à¤µà¥€ à¤¹à¥‹à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¤¾ à¤¤à¤°à¥€à¤•à¤¾ ??

 à¤šà¥€à¤¨à¥€ à¤°à¤£à¤¨à¥€à¤¤à¤¿:-

 1. à¤¸à¤¬à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¤¹à¤²à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤¸à¤•à¥€ à¤¦à¤µà¤¾ à¤¬à¤¨à¤¾à¤ˆà¥¤

 2. à¤«à¤¿à¤° à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¾à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤

 3. à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥€ à¤¦à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¤à¤¾ à¤•à¤¾ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¦à¤°à¥à¤¶à¤¨ à¤•à¤°à¤¤à¥‡ à¤¹à¥à¤ à¤°à¤¾à¤¤à¥‹à¤‚- à¤°à¤¾à¤¤ à¤…à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¤¤à¤¾à¤²à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¾ à¤¨à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¾à¤£ à¤•à¤°à¤µà¤¾ à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ (à¤†à¤–à¤¿à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤µà¥‡ à¤ªà¤¹à¤²à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¤à¥ˆà¤¯à¤¾à¤° à¤¥à¥‡) à¤ªà¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¥‹à¤œà¤¨à¤¾à¤“à¤‚ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤‰à¤ªà¤•à¤°à¤£ à¤•à¤¾ à¤†à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¨à¤¾, à¤¶à¥à¤°à¤®, à¤ªà¤¾à¤¨à¥€ à¤”à¤° à¤¸à¥€à¤µà¥‡à¤œ à¤¨à¥‡à¤Ÿà¤µà¤°à¥à¤• à¤•à¥‹ à¤•à¤¿à¤°à¤¾à¤ à¤ªà¤° à¤²à¥‡à¤¨à¤¾, à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥à¤µà¤¨à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¿à¤¤ à¤¨à¤¿à¤°à¥à¤®à¤¾à¤£ à¤¸à¤¾à¤®à¤—à¥à¤°à¥€ à¤”à¤° à¤à¤• à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤­à¤¾à¤µà¤¶à¤¾à¤²à¥€ à¤®à¤¾à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¸à¥à¤Ÿà¥‰à¤•.. à¤¯à¤¹ à¤¸à¤¬ à¤‰à¤¸ à¤°à¤£à¤¨à¥€à¤¤à¤¿ à¤•à¤¾ à¤¹à¤¿à¤¸à¥à¤¸à¤¾ à¤¥à¥‡à¥¤

 4. à¤ªà¤°à¤¿à¤£à¤¾à¤®à¤¸à¥à¤µà¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤¸à¤¾à¤¥ à¤…à¤°à¤¾à¤œà¤•à¤¤à¤¾ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¥€, à¤–à¤¾à¤¸ à¤•à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤¯à¥‚à¤°à¥‹à¤ª à¤®à¥‡à¤‚à¥¤

 8. à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥‡ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤®à¤¹à¤¾à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤•à¥‹ à¤œà¤²à¥à¤¦à¥€ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤‚à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤¿à¤¤ à¤•à¤° à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¥¤ à¤°à¤¾à¤¤à¥‹à¤‚ à¤°à¤¾à¤¤ à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¨à¤ à¤®à¤°à¥€à¤œ à¤®à¤¿à¤²à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¬à¤¨à¥à¤¦ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤—à¤à¥¤ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤•à¥ˆà¤¸à¥‡ à¤¸à¤®à¥à¤­à¤µ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤œà¤¬à¤•à¤¿ à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€ à¤œà¥ˆà¤¸à¤¾ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¿à¤¤à¤¿ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¸à¤®à¥à¤­à¤¾à¤² à¤ªà¤° à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤†à¤–à¤¿à¤°à¤•à¤¾à¤°, à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤ªà¤¹à¤²à¥‡ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¥€ à¤¤à¥ˆà¤¯à¤¾à¤° à¤¥à¤¾à¥¤

 10. à¤«à¤¿à¤° à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¤à¥à¤°à¤¨à¥à¤¤ à¤¹à¥€ à¤‰à¤¤à¥à¤ªà¤¾à¤¦à¤¨ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤µà¤¾à¤ªà¤¸ à¤œà¥à¤Ÿ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾, à¤œà¤¬à¤•à¤¿ à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤à¤• à¤ à¤¹à¤°à¤¾à¤µ à¤ªà¤° à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤œà¤¹à¤¾à¤‚ à¤à¤• à¤“à¤° à¤¦à¥à¤¨à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¹à¤¾à¤¹à¤¾à¤•à¤¾à¤° à¤®à¤šà¤¾ à¤¹à¥à¤† à¤¹à¥ˆ, à¤µà¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¨à¥‡ à¤…à¤ªà¤¨à¥€ à¤«à¥ˆà¤•à¥à¤Ÿà¥à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤•à¤¾à¤® à¤¶à¥à¤°à¥‚ à¤•à¤°à¤µà¤¾ à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ? à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤‰à¤¨ à¤šà¥€à¤œà¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹ à¤–à¤°à¥€à¤¦à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¤¾ à¤œà¤¿à¤¨à¤•à¥€ à¤•à¥€à¤®à¤¤ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤­à¤¾à¤°à¥€ à¤—à¤¿à¤°à¤¾à¤µà¤Ÿ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤—à¤ˆ à¤¥à¥€ à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤¨à¤•à¥‹ à¤¬à¥‡à¤šà¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¤—à¤¾ à¤œà¤¿à¤¨à¤•à¥€ à¤•à¥€à¤®à¤¤ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¥›à¤¬à¤°à¤¦à¤¸à¥à¤¤ à¤‡à¤œà¤¾à¤«à¤¾ à¤¹à¥à¤† à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤


à¤…à¤¬ à¤¯à¤¦à¤¿ à¤µà¤¿à¤¶à¥à¤µà¤¾à¤¸ à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤°à¤¹à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‹ à¤¤à¥‹...
1999 à¤®à¥‡à¤‚, à¤šà¥€à¤¨à¥€ à¤‰à¤ªà¤¨à¤¿à¤µà¥‡à¤¶à¥‹à¤‚ à¤•à¤¿à¤†à¤“ à¤²à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤‚à¤— à¤”à¤° à¤µà¤¾à¤‚à¤— à¤œà¤¿à¤¯à¤¾à¤‚à¤—à¤¸à¥à¤ˆ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¦à¥à¤µà¤¾à¤°à¤¾ à¤²à¤¿à¤–à¥€ à¤—à¤ˆ à¤ªà¥à¤¸à¥à¤¤à¤•, "à¤…à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¤¿à¤¬à¤‚à¤§à¤¿à¤¤ à¤¯à¥à¤¦à¥à¤§: à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¨à¤·à¥à¤Ÿ à¤•à¤°à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¤¾ à¤®à¤¾à¤¸à¥à¤Ÿà¤° à¤ªà¥à¤²à¤¾à¤¨" à¤•à¥‹ à¤ªà¤¢à¤¼ à¤²à¥‡à¤‚!!* à¤¯à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¬ à¤¤à¤¥à¥à¤¯ à¤µà¤¹à¤¾à¤ à¤®à¥Œà¤œà¥‚à¤¦ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤

à¤œà¤¼à¤°à¤¾ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤¬à¤¾à¤°à¥‡ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¸à¥‹à¤šà¤¿à¤...

 à¤•à¥ˆà¤¸à¥‡ à¤°à¥‚à¤¸ à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤¤à¥à¤¤à¤° à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤•à¥‹à¤µà¤¿à¤¡ 19 à¤¯à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¥‹à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¥‚à¤°à¥€ à¤¤à¤°à¤¹ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¥à¤•à¥à¤¤ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚? à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚à¤•à¤¿ à¤µà¥‡ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤•à¤Ÿà¥à¤Ÿà¤° à¤¸à¤¹à¤¯à¥‹à¤—à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤  à¤‡à¤¨ 2 à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤à¤• à¤­à¥€ à¤®à¤¾à¤®à¤²à¥‡ à¤•à¥€ à¤¸à¥‚à¤šà¤¨à¤¾ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤®à¤¿à¤²à¥€à¥¤  à¤¦à¥‚à¤¸à¤°à¥€ à¤“à¤° à¤¦à¤•à¥à¤·à¤¿à¤£ à¤•à¥‹à¤°à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ / à¤¯à¥‚à¤¨à¤¾à¤‡à¤Ÿà¥‡à¤¡ à¤•à¤¿à¤‚à¤—à¤¡à¤® / à¤‡à¤Ÿà¤²à¥€ / à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¥‡à¤¨ à¤”à¤° à¤à¤¶à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤—à¤‚à¤­à¥€à¤° à¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤¸à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤­à¤¾à¤µà¤¿à¤¤ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚à¤•à¤¿ à¤¯à¥‡ à¤¸à¤¬ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¤à¤¿à¤¸à¥à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤§à¥€ à¤¹à¥ˆ..
 
à¤•à¥ˆà¤¸à¥‡ à¤¹à¥à¤† à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤…à¤šà¤¾à¤¨à¤• à¤˜à¤¾à¤¤à¤• à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤®à¥à¤•à¥à¤¤?

à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤•à¤¹à¥‡à¤—à¤¾ à¤•à¤¿ à¤‰à¤¨à¤•à¥‡ à¤ªà¥à¤°à¤¾à¤°à¤‚à¤­à¤¿à¤• à¤‰à¤ªà¤¾à¤¯ à¤¬à¤¹à¥à¤¤ à¤•à¤ à¥‹à¤° à¤¥à¥‡ à¤”à¤° à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤•à¥‹ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤•à¥à¤·à¥‡à¤¤à¥à¤°à¥‹à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤¬à¤‚à¤¦ à¤¯à¤¾à¤¨à¥‡ à¤²à¥‹à¤•à¤¡à¤¾à¤‰à¤¨ à¤•à¤° à¤¦à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¥à¤¾à¥¤ à¤ªà¤°à¤¨à¥à¤¤à¥ à¤¯à¥‡ à¤œà¤µà¤¾à¤¬ à¤¬à¥œà¤¾ à¤¹à¥€  à¤®à¤œà¤¾à¤•à¤¿à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ..à¤à¤¸à¤¾ à¤¹à¥‹à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¤à¥‹ à¤¬à¤¾à¤•à¥€ à¤•à¥‡ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶à¥‹à¤‚ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤­à¥€ à¤¯à¤¹ à¤‡à¤¤à¤¨à¤¾ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤«à¥ˆà¤²à¤¤à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤à¤• à¤¶à¤¹à¤° à¤¤à¤• à¤¹à¥€ à¤¸à¥€à¤®à¤¿à¤¤ à¤°à¤¹à¤¤à¤¾à¥¤ à¤¯à¤¹ 100% à¤¸à¤¤à¥à¤¯ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤•à¤¿ à¤µà¥‡ à¤µà¤¾à¤¯à¤°à¤¸ à¤•à¥‡ à¤à¤‚à¤Ÿà¥€ à¤¡à¥‹à¤¡ à¤•à¤¾ à¤‰à¤ªà¤¯à¥‹à¤— à¤•à¤° à¤°à¤¹à¥‡ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤

 à¤¬à¥€à¤œà¤¿à¤‚à¤— à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤•à¥‹à¤ˆ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤®à¤¾à¤°à¤¾ à¤—à¤¯à¤¾? à¤•à¥‡à¤µà¤² à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤¹à¥€ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚?  à¤¦à¤¿à¤²à¤šà¤¸à¥à¤ª à¤µà¤¿à¤šà¤¾à¤° à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤¯à¥‡ ...à¤–à¥ˆà¤°, à¤µà¥à¤¹à¤¾à¤¨ à¤…à¤¬ à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤¾à¤ªà¤¾à¤° à¤•à¥‡ à¤²à¤¿à¤ à¤–à¥à¤² à¤—à¤¯à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤ à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤”à¤° à¤‰à¤ªà¤°à¥à¤¯à¥à¤•à¥à¤¤ à¤¸à¤­à¥€ à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶ à¤†à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤¿à¤• à¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¤à¤¬à¤¾à¤¹ à¤¹à¥ˆà¤‚à¥¤  à¤œà¤²à¥à¤¦ à¤¹à¥€ à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¥€ à¤…à¤°à¥à¤¥à¤µà¥à¤¯à¤µà¤¸à¥à¤¥à¤¾ à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤•à¥€ à¤¯à¥‹à¤œà¤¨à¤¾ à¤•à¥‡ à¤…à¤¨à¥à¤¸à¤¾à¤° à¤¢à¤¹ à¤œà¤¾à¤à¤—à¥€à¥¤  à¤šà¥€à¤¨ à¤œà¤¾à¤¨à¤¤à¤¾ à¤¹à¥ˆ à¤•à¤¿ à¤µà¤¹ à¤…à¤®à¥‡à¤°à¤¿à¤•à¤¾ à¤•à¥‹ à¤¸à¥ˆà¤¨à¥à¤¯ à¤°à¥‚à¤ª à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¨à¤¹à¥€à¤‚ à¤¹à¤°à¤¾ à¤¸à¤•à¤¤à¤¾ à¤•à¥à¤¯à¥‹à¤‚à¤•à¤¿ à¤µà¤°à¥à¤¤à¤®à¤¾à¤¨ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤‡à¤¸ à¤¹à¤¿à¤¸à¤¾à¤¬ à¤¸à¥‡ à¤…à¤®à¤°à¥€à¤•à¤¾ à¤µà¤¿à¤¶à¥à¤µ à¤®à¥‡à¤‚ à¤¸à¤¬à¤¸à¥‡ à¤¬à¥œà¤¾ à¤¤à¤¾à¤•à¤¤à¤µà¤° à¤¦à¥‡à¤¶ à¤¹à¥ˆà¥¤

Dear friends
Our Doctor who recovered from Corona illness and recovered in double quick time had inhaled Steam.
The doctors at IDH Corona centre too are continually inhaling steam.

Steaming raises the temperature of lungs, throat and mouth so that if the virus is already there it gets inactivate due to high temperature.

Yes thatâ€™s true as viruses sit in the throat first. 

Thatâ€™s why even if there is someone sneezing in your office and you come home and inhale and gargle with warm water and salt, usually you will not get the flu. 

I recommend for everyone who is able to do it - 
1. Use steam inhalation everyday - morning and evening if possible,
2. Gargle with warm water and salt daily - morning and evening if possible.

This is a good daily practice which will improve your overall well-being and can be continued even after COVID19 ends.

Please also pass this information for the benefit of others.

4/2/20, 6:02 PM - +91 99585 15757: Forwarded as received:

Few lessons learnt in past few days: 

 1. United States is no longer the world's leading country.
 2. China won the 3rd World War without firing a missile and no one could handle it.
 3. Europeans are not as educated as they appear.
4. We can survive vacations without trips to Europe and USA.
5. Rich people are in fact less immune than the poor.
 6. Human beings are opportunistic and despicable no matter their socioeconomic position when prices are rising.
7. No priest, poojari, Imam,  Pope or God saved patients .
 8. Humans are the real viruses on the planet.
9. We can spend Billions of Rupees on poor without red tapism.
10. Health professionals are worth more than a footballer.
11. Oil is worthless in a society without consumption.
12. How animals feel in the zoo.
13. The planet  regenerates quickly without humans into play.
14. Majority of people can work from home.
15. We and the kids can survive without junk food.
16. Prisoners in jails for petty crimes can be released.
17. Living a hygienic life is not difficult.
18. Only women are not supposed to know cooking.
19. There are a lot of good people in the World.
20. If you build more schools, you have to construct less hospitals.
21. Media is bullshit.

4/3/20, 1:25 PM - Vikas Vidhyarthy Civil: I don't know who wrote this, but it's beautiful.. â™¥

We fell asleep in one world, and woke up in another.

Suddenly Disney is out of magic,
Paris is no longer romantic,
New York doesn't stand up anymore,
the Chinese wall is no longer a fortress, and Mecca is empty.

Hugs & kisses suddenly become weapons, and not visiting parents & friends becomes an act of love.

Suddenly you realise that power, beauty & money are worthless, and can't get you the oxygen you're fighting for.

The world continues its life and it is beautiful. It only puts humans in cages. I think it's sending us a message:

"You are not necessary. The air, earth, water and sky without you are fine. When you come back, remember that you are my guests. Not my masters."

4/6/20, 7:44 AM - +91 99585 15757: India seems to be coronavirus free even though it is a close neighbor of China. 

There is a lot of speculation and eyebrows raised as to why this is so. 

Various reasons are being put out:

1) The Indian gene is Covid-19 resistant.
2) The low level of hygiene has made Indians immune to this virus.
3) The Indian curry might have ingredients that are antiviral.
4) Maybe the high level of chillies in our food help prevent lung infection by C-19.
5) The Indian habit of washing their hands and everything else may play a role.
6) Most Indians eat hot food and do not share their food. This prevents spread of infection.
7) The "Namaste"  helps, as people don't touch each other.
8) India has a warmer climate that is killing the C-19.
9) Indians are a lot vegetarian and even the non vegetarians can switch to vegetables. The meat eating has drastically dropped in India after the C-19 scare as per statistics.

In fact WHO and China are really wondering and trying to understand how a country of 1.38 billion can be coronavirus free ! 
God only knows and hope it stays this way.

 On account of data aggregation on the Virtual Class Activities, it is planned to use the Academia Portal (official academic erp in KTR).
 As an initial process, all the faculty members of RMP,NCR,CDP campuses are to be onboarded to the portal through an official invitation email.
 I've attached the instructions of the onboarding process and gaining access to the Academia Portal along with this email. Please go through the instructions and follow the same to onboard the portal.
 It is just is in 3 simple steps,
1. You will receive an official invite from the mail: engage.et@srrmist.edu.in
2. You have to accept the invitation and create your own password
3. Access the Academia portal through the url: creator.zoho.com

Detailed instructions are attached for your reference.

Email invitations will be sent by today 7pm. The invitation mail will be active for 6 hours. So please activate your account. You may update data after receiving our instructions.

Welcome to Academia !!

6/15/20, 5:50 PM - +91 99999 90901: To all parentsğŸ™

There was a very brilliant boy, he always scored 100% in Science.

Got Selected for IIT Madras and scored excellent in IIT.

Went to the University of California for MBA.
Got a high paying job in America and settled there.

Married a Beautiful Tamil Girl.

Bought a 5 room big house and luxury cars.
He had everything that make him successful but a few years ago he committed suicide after shooting his wife and children.

*WHAT WENT WRONG?*

California Institute of Clinical Psychology Studied his case and found *â€œwhat went wrong?â€*

The researcher met the boy's friends and family and found that he lost his job due to Americaâ€™s economic crisis and he had to sit without a job for a long time. 

After even reducing his previous salary amount, he didn't get any job. 

Then his house installment broke and he and his family lost the home. 

They survived a few months with less money and then he and his wife together decided to commit suicide. 

He first shot his wife and children and then shot himself.

The case concluded that the man was Programmed for *success* but he was not *trained for handling failures*.

Now let's come to the actual question.

*What are the habits of highly successful people?*

First of all, I want to tell you that if you have achieved everything, there is a chance to lose everything, nobody knows when the next economic crisis will hit the world. 

*The best success habit is getting trained for handling failures*.

I want to request every parent, please do not only program your child to be *successful* but *teach them how to handle failures* and also teach them proper lessons about life. 

Learning high-level science and maths will help them to clear competitive exams but a knowledge about life will help them to face every problem.

Teach them about how *money works* instead of teaching them to *work for money*. 

Help them in finding their passion because these degrees will not help them in the next economic crisis and we donâ€™t know when the next crisis will hit the world.

*"Success is a lousy teacher. Failure teaches you more."*

6/28/20, 6:45 PM - Bharati Chandrayan: This message was deleted
6/29/20, 11:48 AM - Dinesh Babu: Subject:IT Service Enhancement-NetID integration for E-Varsity.

Dear All,

Greetings from ITKM Team!!!

At ITKM we are working on a single-sign-on project since March-2019.

The objective of this project is to overcome the challenges facing by the organization/employee/students to manage multiple user ID & password for various applications, e-mail, networks, which is being used by SRM community over years.

We at ITKM receive numerous calls on resetting password, this is productivity loss for the users. An OTP based self service portal (https://ssp.srmist.edu.in) has been introduced in Jun`19. Anyone can reset password without any ITKM invention using this portal.

As initial step we have introduced NetID as single for every purpose. We have integrated NetID with E-mail & TeamDeck application & password reset portal. All future SRMIST application will be developed (i.e URP, mobile app) will be integrated with NetID.

As part of Single Sign On (SSO) initiative, from 1st July 2020 onwards you will be using your NetID credentials to login in E-Varsity.

The Existing employee id based username and password will not work for SRMIST user after 1st July 2020.

Thanks and Regards,
Dinesh Babu. K
Network Engineer & ERP In-charge

7/12/20, 7:22 AM - +91 96399 57994: Covid Medical kit Required at home:

1. Paracetamol
2. Betadine for mouthwash and gargle
3. Vitamin C and D3 
5. B complex 
6. Vapour+ capsules for steam
7. Oximeter 
8. Oxygen cylinder (for emergency only)
9. arogya Setu app 
10.Breathing Exercises 

Covid Three stages:

1. Covid only in nose - recovery  time is half a day. (Steam inhaling), vitamin C. Usually no fever. Asymptomatic. 

2. Covid in throat - sore throat, recovery time 1 day (hot water gargle, warm water to drink, if temp then paracetamol. Vitamin C, Bcomplex. If severe than antibiotic. 

3. Covid in lungs- coughing and breathlessness 4 to 5 days. (Vitamin C, B complex, hot water gargle, oximeter, paracetamol, cylinder if severe, lot of liquid required, deep breathing exercise.

Stage when to approach hospital:
Monitor the oxygen level. If it goes near 43 (normal 98-100) then you need oxygen cylinder. If available at home, then no hospital else admit.

*Stay healthy, Stay Safe!*
 Please fwd to your contacts in India. You never know who it may help. 
Tata Group has started good initiative, they are providing free doctors consultation online through chats. This facility is started for you so that you need not to go out for doctors and you will be safe at home.

Below is the link, I reqest everyone to take benefit of this facility.
https://www.tatahealth.com/online-doctor-consultation/general-physician

Advice from inside isolation hospitals, we can do at home
 Medicines that are taken in isolation hospitals
 1. Vitamin C-1000
 2. Vitamin E (E)
 3. From (10 to 11) hours, sitting in the sunlight for 15-20 minutes.
 4. Egg meal once ..
 5. We take a rest / sleep a minimum of 7-8 hours
 6. We drink 1.5 liters of water daily
 7. All meals should be warm (not cold).
 And that's all we do in the hospital to strengthen the immune system

 Note that the pH of coronavirus varies from 5.5 to 8.5

 Therefore, all we have to do to eliminate the virus is to consume more alkaline foods above the acidity level of the virus.
 Such as :
 Bananas 
 Green lemon - 9.9 pH
 Yellow Lemon - 8.2 pH
 Avocado - 15.6 pH
 * Garlic - 13.2 pH
 * Mango - 8.7 pH
 * Tangerine - 8.5 pH
 * Pineapple - 12.7 pH
 * Watercress - 22.7 pH
 * Oranges - 9.2 pH

 How to know that you are infected with corona virus?

 1. Itchy throat
 2. Dry throat
 3. Dry cough
 4. High temperature
 5. Shortness of breath
 6. Loss of smell ....
 And lemon with warm water eliminates the virus at the beginning before reaching the lungs ...
 Do not keep this information to yourself. Provide it to all your family and friends.

7/20/20, 12:29 PM - DR Sir WhatsApp No: Dear faculty members 

Please note and understand clearly the following -

Procedures for taking admission 

1. Immediate admission 
Students and parents can come to our campus with mark sheet with 50% in PCM for all engineering courses .

Tuition fee in the form of DD in favour of SRM IST payable at NewDelhi must be submitted.

Receipt can be taken immediately 

2. For those who cannot come personally and want to take admissions 
Mark sheet can be mailed to dean admissions 
Mail ID - dean.admissions.ncr@srmist.edu.in 

After verification of the marksheet and the student is found to have 50% in PCM he / she will be mailed asking to submit the fees. 

RTGS transcation can be done.Name: SRM Institute of Science and Technology
Bank Name: City Union Bank Ltd
Account No: 102109000066529
IFSC code: CIUB0000102
Address: 18/7, Arya Samaj Road, Karol Bagh, New Delhi - 110005

3. No- Paper admission process -

Admission can be taken through our website www.srmup.in
Fee can be paid online through our website.

This is applicable for all three admission procedures. Receipts will be provided for fee payment.

All faculty members and admission counsellors should understand this and explain approximately to candidates and parents.
Information given to aspirants should be crystal clear and ease their admission process.

Deputy Registrar

Male Faculty- 
Coat -  Black, Brown or Blue
Plain shirt - white or blue colour only 
Tie and ID card

Female Faculty- 
Formal Saree & ID card 

Lab Technicians 
Shirt & Pant in formal colour and Tie.

As instructed on 23/7/2020, no leave of any form will be sanctioned on these two days.

The photo shoot is being done for our new website and sooner we provide these photos our website will be professional and full fledged.

7/30/20, 10:25 AM - DR Sir WhatsApp No: *Very important decision by Modi Government*

New Education Policy 2020 is announced

1. 10+2 board structure is   dropped
2. New school structure will be 5+3+3+4
3. Upto 5 pre school, 6 to 8 Mid School, 8 to 11 High School , 12 onwards Graduation
4. Any Degree will be 4 years
5. 6th std onwards vocational courses available
6. From 8th to 11 students can choose subjects 
7. All graduation course will have major and minor
Example - science student can have Physics as Major and Music as minor also. Any combination he can choose
8. All higher education will be governed by only one authority. 
9. UGC AICTE will be merged.
10. All University government, private, Open, Deemed, Vocational etc will have same grading and other rules.
11. New Teacher Training board will be setup for all kinds of teachers in country, no state can change
12. Same level of Accreditation to any collage , based on its rating collage will get autonomous rights and funds.
13. New Basic learning program will be created by government for parents to teach children upto 3 years in home and for pre school 3 to 6
14. Multiple entry and exit from any course 
15. Credit system for graduation for each year student will get some credits which he can utilize if he takes break in course and come back again to complete course
16. All schools exams will be semester wise twise a year
17. The syllabus will be reduced to core knowledge of any subject only
18. More focus on student practical and application knowledge
19. For any graduation course if student complete only one year he will get a basic certificate, if he complete two years then he will get Diploma certificate and if he complete full course then he will get degree certificate. So no year of any student will ve vested if he break the course in between.
20.All the graduation course feed of all Universities will be govern by single authority with capping on each course.

Now we can hope our education system will be at par with moder countries and future of our children will be bright.

8/4/20, 8:21 PM - Dinesh Babu: Dear All,

The unscheduled maintenance activity has been completed and the SSP Service is back to normal.

We(ITKM) request you to forward the below mentioned process to students to reset their official mail-id password.

Kindly update your personal contact details (e-mail and contact number) in the Student Information Portal (e-varsity) for resetting password in the Self Service Portal (SSP).

E-varsity (Student Information Portal) URL: https://evarsity.srmist.edu.in/srmsip/

Self Service Portal URL: https://ssp.srmist.edu.in/

1. To update personal contact details in E-varsity

A. Login Student information portal (E-varsity) by using the username and password
B. Click updates menu --> Update Personal Contact.
C. To modify e-mail ID and contact number.
D. Click send OTP and then enter the OTP click submit

2. To reset official SRM IST e-mail password

A. Open https://ssp.srmist.edu.in/  in any browser.
B. Choose Reset Password after Enter your Net ID and captcha click Submit
C. Enter the masked letter in the mail id -->Click Send OTP and Enter the OTP --> Submit.
D. Create the New Password and Confirm Password -> Submit

Note: Please do not use your name as password and follow the password complexity as mentioned in Self Service Portal.

Thanks & regards
Dinesh Babu.K
Network Engineer and ERP (NCR Campus Co-ordinator) .

This is to inform you that we have planned to have one to one Zoom Meeting with the prospective aspirants of our NCR  campus who can be counselled at this point of time and thus making them take admissions at NCR campus.
The meeting will be held in batches of 20-25 candidates for a duration of 30 minutes. 
10 such batches will be counselled each day starting from tomorrow from 9.30am onwards.

The Zoom Meeting has been titled 
â€œ ADMISSION cum CAREER GUIDANCEâ€.

All our Deans will be present for the meeting and HoD, CDC & Placement will be in the meeting.

9/17/20, 8:39 AM - Naresh Sharma: *A very interesting story*

One Sunday morning, a wealthy man sat in his balcony enjoying sunshine and his coffee when a little ant caught his eye which was going from one side to the other side of the balcony carrying a big leaf several times more than its size.

 The man watched it for more than an hour. He saw that the ant faced many obstacles during its journey, paused, took a diversion and then continued towards destination.

At one point the tiny creature came across a crack in the floor. It paused for a little while, analyzed and then laid the huge leaf over the crack, walked over the leaf, picked the leaf on the other side then continued its journey.

The man was captivated by the cleverness of the ant, one of Godâ€™s tiniest creatures. The incident left the man in awe and forced him to contemplate over the miracle of Creation. It showed the Greatness of the Creator. 

In front of his eyes there was this tiny creature of God, lacking in size yet equipped with a brain to analyze, contemplate, reason, explore, discover and overcome.

A while later the man saw that the creature had reached its destination â€“ a tiny hole in the floor which was entrance to its underground dwelling.

 And it was at this point that the antâ€™s shortcoming that it shared with the man was revealed. 

How could the ant carry into the tiny hole the large leaf that it had managed to carefully bring to the destination? It simply couldn't! So the tiny creature, after all the painstaking and hard work and exercising great skills, overcoming all the difficulties along the way, just left behind the large leaf and went home empty-handed.

The ant had not thought about the end before it began its challenging journey and in the end the large leaf was nothing more than a burden to it. 

The creature had no option, but to leave it behind to reach its destination. 

The man learned a great lesson that day.

That is the truth about our lives too.

We worry about our family, we worry about our job, we worry about how to earn more money, we worry about where we should live, what kind of vehicle to buy, what kind of dresses to wear, what gadgets to upgrade, only to abandon all these things when we reach our destination â€“ We donâ€™t realize in our lifeâ€™s journey that these are just burdens that we are carrying with utmost care and fear of losing them, only to find that at the end they are useless and we canâ€™t take them with us.....

9/21/20, 1:15 PM - +91 93548 77129: Dear All, 

Computer Society of India (CSI) is now active in SRM Institute of Science and Technology, Delhi NCR Campus.
*We need to form a CSI Student Chapter at our campus*
for which I would request all HODs of  various branches to circulate google form (link is given with this msg) and poster of CSI among all students. Interested students can fill up the form.
I would also request all of you to motivate students to come forward and be a part of CSI so that we all can work as one team.
We are trying to do publicity on social media through Instagram, Facebook and LinkedIn.
I am sharing the links of social Medias with this message, 
I would request you to like the page and tell the same to students
Information of CSI
ABOUT:
Computer Society of India (CSI) is the first and largest body of computer professionals in India. It was started on 6 March 1965 by a few computer professionals and has now grown to be the national body representing computer professionals.

VISION:
The Computer Society of India is a non-profit professional society and meet to exchange views and information learn and share ideas. The wide spectrum of members is committed to the advancement of theory and practice of Computer Engineering and Technology Systems, Science and Engineering, Information Processing and related Arts and Sciences.

MISSION:
- Facilitate Research, Knowledge Sharing, Learning and Career Enhancement among all categories of IT professionals.
- Inspire, nurture and assist students to integrate into the IT community.
- Percolate benefits of IT advancement to all sections of Indian Society.

Important Links:
Instagram: https://instagram.com/teamcsi_srm?igshid=nt1uftgl7uja
LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/company/csi-srmncr
Facebook: https://www.facebook.com/TeamCsiSrmNcr/
Join by filling the Google form: https://forms.gle/9MJoh7uzW8PNw6jj6

10/20/20, 9:59 AM - DR Sir WhatsApp No: Dear Nitin

The basic purpose of media coverage for any programme is to broadcast our campus activities amongst public. However this task should be done appropriately.

Whenever any activities may it be co-curricular or extracurricular, the focus should be on the invited guest and not the internal members of our campus.
For instance, the photo of the chief guest for the FDP Programme Prof Rajat Gupta should have been on the news instead of mine.

The Director of NIT Mizoram being present for our programme is the news and this is what people want to see and listen from a brand like us.

The news of FDP with my photograph is totally mindless. 

Therefore in all future Campus activities and programmes where news / photographs are being sent to media, prior permission should be taken from my office. 
Without approvals no photographs shall be sent to media.

All the Hods and event coordinators should note this and adhere without deviations. 


Deputy Registrar

10/24/20, 5:15 PM - +91 94133 50811: Dear Students,

Team ISTE 'SRM is very happy to invite first year students to participate in one of the biggest annual event by us. We present to you the event *Mock Placement '20 + workshop on competitive programming*. Mock Placement will give you the experience of how real placements happen. Their will be a exclusive workshop on competitive programming after the Mock Placement. Please find various details about event and ISTE below.

*WHAT IS ISTE?*
I.S.T.E (Indian Society for Technical Education) is a national, professional, non-profit making, government aided society, started in 1941 as the "Association of Principals of Technical Education (A.P.T.I)". The Students' chapter of ISTE was started in 2007 in our campus.

*OUR VISION AND MISSION:*
Colleges only focusing on theoretical knowledge and not on what the industry really expects from a professional, ISTE'S main objective is to assist and contribute in the production and development of the professionals in the industry. We conduct many events which target a particular set of skills which help in developing general logic, perception and creativity among the students, like workshops for embedded systems, digital marketing, programming languages like C++, Java, HTML, various quizzes, Forums and much more. In a nutshell I.S.T.E has striven to make every student at par with any other professional of that particular field.


*Please refer to various details below about the event:* ğŸ‘‡

*Mock Placement *+ Workshop(Competitive Programming) :* You should attend this Mock Placement event because it will give you an idea about the placement process so that you don't have to see it on YouTube, attend webinars or contact seniors to know about it. You can simply attend the event and get to know everything about it. Also we have 2 days workshop on Competitive Programming provided by our official partner *REGex*, for you all where you'll be taught competitive programming from basic to top level along with hands-on practice.
